<paragraph id="E97036DD3F0FFF98FF76FC1FFD57FC52" blockId="58.[151,1437,921,1595]" box="[151,695,921,948]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
Size. Known adult size about 
<quantity id="2E379B383F0FFF98FE07FC1FFDCAFC55" box="[486,554,921,948]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" unit="cm" value="11.0">11 cm</quantity>
total length.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A1D565563F0FFF98FF26FC3BFE2DF9DA" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" type="description">
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F0FFF98FF26FC3BFDF9FB86" blockId="58.[151,1437,921,1595]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
Morphology. D VI + I,13–14; A I,13; P 17–19. Medium-sized goby, snout moderately short but longer than the eye diameter, with a moderately steep profile. Caudal peduncle deep, but lower than body depth. Dorsal fins of similar height, the first dorsal fin may be slightly higher, with more or less rounded distal edge and no elongate spines. Caudal fin rounded. Scales present on body and on predorsal area, usually visible on photographs at least on body (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F0FFF98FEE0FBCBFDEEFB86" author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Miller, P. J." box="[257,526,1101,1127]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" pagination="231 - 239" refId="ref58118" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Miller, P. J. (2000) A new species of Gobius (Teleostei: Gobiidae) from the northern Adriatic Sea. Cybium, 24 (3), 231 - 239." type="journal article" year="2000">Kovačić &amp; Miller 2000</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F0FFF98FF26FBF7FB0FFAFA" blockId="58.[151,1437,921,1595]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
Live coloration. Head and body on back pale to fawn, pearly white ventrally, with 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F0FFF98FB8CFBF7FDE8FB4E" bold="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">irregular orange blotches arranged in longitudinal series</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F0FFF98FDF6FB13FD8BFB4E" box="[535,619,1173,1199]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1981,2005]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,1110,1958]" captionTargetId="figure-40@22.[157,1429,1110,1958]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 18. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Gobius kolombatovici. Photo by S. Le Bris, Marseille, Southern France." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601623" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601623/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F0FFF98FD61FB13FB5CFB4E" bold="true" box="[640,1212,1173,1199]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Snout with a conspicuous, V-shaped orange line</emphasis>
. A broad horizontal stripe across eye and a continuous and well-marked orange oculoscapular line from behind eye to above pectoral-fin base. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F0FFF98FF36FB5BFEC3FAFA" bold="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">First dorsal fin with a distinct oval blackish blotch between the third and fourth (or fifth) interspinous membranes</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F0FFF98FED3FA87FE64FAFA" box="[306,388,1281,1307]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1981,2005]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,1110,1958]" captionTargetId="figure-40@22.[157,1429,1110,1958]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 18. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Gobius kolombatovici. Photo by S. Le Bris, Marseille, Southern France." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601623" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601623/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F0FFF98FE7AFA87FD47FAFA" author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Miller, P. J." box="[411,679,1281,1307]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" pagination="231 - 239" refId="ref58118" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Miller, P. J. (2000) A new species of Gobius (Teleostei: Gobiidae) from the northern Adriatic Sea. Cybium, 24 (3), 231 - 239." type="journal article" year="2000">Kovačić &amp; Miller 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F0FFF98FD50FA84FC1CFAFA" author="Francour, P. &amp; Mangialajo, L." box="[689,1020,1281,1308]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" pagination="389 - 390" refId="ref54609" refString="Francour, P. &amp; Mangialajo, L. (2007) Gobius kolombatovici, a common species of Gobiidae in the north-western Mediterranean Sea. Cybium, 31 (3), 389 - 390. https: // doi. org / 10.26028 / cybium / 2007 - 313 - 008" type="journal article" year="2007">Francour &amp; Mangialajo 2007</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F0FFF98FBE9FA87FB03FAFA" author="Renoult, J. P. &amp; Pillon, R. &amp; Kovacic, M. &amp; Louisy, P." box="[1032,1251,1281,1308]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" refId="ref63723" refString="Renoult, J. P., Pillon, R., Kovacic, M. &amp; Louisy, P. (2022) Frontiers in Fishwatching Series - Gobies of North-eastern Atlantic and the Mediterranean: Gobius and Thorogobius. Les cahiers de la fondation Biotope. [in press]" type="book" year="2022">
Renoult 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F0FFF98FB86FA84FB78FAFA" box="[1127,1176,1281,1307]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">et al</emphasis>
. 2022
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F0FFF98FF26FAA3FD77FAA1" blockId="58.[151,1437,921,1595]" box="[199,663,1317,1344]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
Similar species. 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F0FFF98FE9EFAA3FD70FADE" authorityName="Benthic" baseAuthorityName="Kolombatovic" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[383,656,1317,1343]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Thorogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrolepis">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F0FFF98FE9EFAA3FD70FADE" box="[383,656,1317,1343]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Thorogobius macrolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F0FFF98FF26FACFFCBFFA4A" blockId="58.[151,1437,921,1595]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
Habitat. Infralittoral and circalittoral species, known from 
<quantity id="2E379B383F0FFF98FCBEFACFFC23FA85" box="[863,963,1353,1380]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.1" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" unit="m" value="51.0" valueMax="90.0" valueMin="12.0">12–90 m</quantity>
depth. Typically found on patches of soft bottoms in steep rocky areas, often on coarse shell sand at the bottom of rocky or coralligenous walls, close to shelter (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F0FFF98FF11FA17FE1CFA4A" author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Miller, P. J." box="[240,508,1425,1451]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" pagination="231 - 239" refId="ref58118" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Miller, P. J. (2000) A new species of Gobius (Teleostei: Gobiidae) from the northern Adriatic Sea. Cybium, 24 (3), 231 - 239." type="journal article" year="2000">Kovačić &amp; Miller 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F0FFF98FDE6FA14FCB3FA4A" author="Francour, P. &amp; Mangialajo, L." box="[519,851,1425,1452]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" pagination="389 - 390" refId="ref54609" refString="Francour, P. &amp; Mangialajo, L. (2007) Gobius kolombatovici, a common species of Gobiidae in the north-western Mediterranean Sea. Cybium, 31 (3), 389 - 390. https: // doi. org / 10.26028 / cybium / 2007 - 313 - 008" type="journal article" year="2007">Francour &amp; Mangialajo 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F0FFF98FF26FA33FE2DF9DA" blockId="58.[151,1437,921,1595]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
Geographic distribution. Scattered records in the Mediterranean Sea: western Mediterranean (e.g., Columbretes and Balearic Islands in Spain: 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F0FFF98FE1CFA5FFCACFA12" author="Kersting, D. K. &amp; Ballesteros, E." box="[509,844,1497,1523]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" refId="ref57223" refString="Kersting, D. K. &amp; Ballesteros, E. (2010) Gobius kolombatovici, primera cita en las costas ibericas, Islas Columbretes (Mediterraneo noroccidental). XVI Simposio Iberico de Estudios de Biologia Marina, Alicante, Espana, 6 - 10 Septiembre 2010, 181." type="journal volume" year="2010">Kersting &amp; Ballesteros 2010</bibRefCitation>
); Ligurian (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F0FFF98FC35FA5FFACBFA12" author="Francour, P. &amp; Mangialajo, L." box="[980,1323,1497,1523]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" pagination="389 - 390" refId="ref54609" refString="Francour, P. &amp; Mangialajo, L. (2007) Gobius kolombatovici, a common species of Gobiidae in the north-western Mediterranean Sea. Cybium, 31 (3), 389 - 390. https: // doi. org / 10.26028 / cybium / 2007 - 313 - 008" type="journal article" year="2007">Francour &amp; Mangialajo 2007</bibRefCitation>
), Adriatic (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F0FFF98FF7EFA7BFE50F9F6" author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Miller, P. J." box="[159,432,1533,1559]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" pagination="231 - 239" refId="ref58118" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Miller, P. J. (2000) A new species of Gobius (Teleostei: Gobiidae) from the northern Adriatic Sea. Cybium, 24 (3), 231 - 239." type="journal article" year="2000">Kovačić &amp; Miller 2000</bibRefCitation>
), Ionian (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F0FFF98FDFCFA7BFCA9F9F9" author="Tiralongo, F. &amp; Pagano, A." box="[541,841,1533,1560]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" pagination="682 - 702" refId="ref64992" refString="Tiralongo, F. &amp; Pagano, A. (2015) On the presence of Gobius kolombatovici in the Ionian Sea. In: Crocetta, F., Agius, D., Balistreri, P., Bariche, M., Bayhan, Y. K .., Cakir, M .., Ciriaco, S .., Corsini-Foka, M .., Deidun, A .., El Zrelli, R .., Erguden, D .., Evans, J .., Ghelia, M .., Giavasi, M .., Kleitou, P .., Kondylatos, G .., Lipej, L .., Mifsud, C .., Ozvarol, Y .., Pagano, A .., Portelli, P .., Poursanidis, D .., Rabaoui, L .., Schembri, P. J .., Taskin, E .., Tiralongo, F. &amp; Zenetos, A., New Mediterranean Marine Biodiversity Records, October, 2015. Mediterranean Marine Science, 16 (3), pp. 682 - 702. https: // doi. org / 10.12681 / mms. 1477" type="journal article" year="2015">Tiralongo &amp; Pagano 2015</bibRefCitation>
) and Aegean seas (Bilecenoğlu 2013), and 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F0FFF98FADBFA7BFA7CF9F6" box="[1338,1436,1533,1559]" name="Lebanon" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Lebanon</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F0FFF98FF7EF9A7FE20F9DA" author="Bitar, G. &amp; Badreddine, A." box="[159,448,1569,1595]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" pagination="1 - 128" refId="ref52096" refString="Bitar, G. &amp; Badreddine, A. (2021) An updated checklist of the marine fishes in Lebanon. An answer to Bariche and Fricke (2020): &quot; The marine ichthyofauna of Lebanon: an annotated checklist, history, biogeography, and conservation status &quot;. Zootaxa, 5010 (1), 1 - 128. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 5010.1.1" type="journal article" year="2021">Bitar &amp; Badreddine 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
